1
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,940
=About Love=

2
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 10=

3
00:01:24,350 --> 00:01:25,430
Breast cancer?

4
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:28,950
I don't even know
how many days I've left.

5
00:01:31,590 --> 00:01:33,280
For someone like me,

6
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:35,870
love always feels out of reach.

7
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:38,310
But my boyfriend

8
00:01:38,310 --> 00:01:39,680
is such a kind soul.

9
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,870
He's been healing me

10
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:44,710
and lifting my spirits.

11
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:48,070
Sometimes I think,

12
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:50,870
even if it's just for him,

13
00:01:52,710 --> 00:01:54,200
I would live well.

14
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,040
Right now,

15
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:00,120
you need to follow the doctor's treatment.

16
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,430
Everything else doesn't really matter.

17
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:05,510
I just don't want to make him sad.

18
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:07,350
He's such a good guy.

19
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,560
He could've been with
someone so much better.

20
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,840
I don't want to hold him back.

21
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,960
Honestly, I've been thinking
about leaving him.

22
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,560
But he's just too stubborn.

23
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,240
Plus, I still care about him.

24
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:30,080
It's hard to push away someone you love.

25
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,870
So, you're saying...

26
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,870
you want me to help you

27
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:38,870
to get him to leave you, right?

28
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,750
All I want is to make up my mind.

29
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:51,240
If he doesn't care about me that much

30
00:02:54,030 --> 00:02:55,310
and falls for someone else,

31
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:58,240
honestly, I'd be okay with that.

32
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:02,240
If he never falls for anyone else,

33
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:07,560
I'll stay with him
for the rest of my life.

34
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,590
But I still feel bad for him.

35
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,030
One day, he'll face the fact
that I'll be gone.

36
00:03:25,630 --> 00:03:26,800
My sister...

37
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,960
She cares about me way too much.

38
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:31,030
Sorry.

39
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,870
So, you still want my help, right?

40
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:42,870
I know you're not in a place

41
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,590
to help with something like this right now.

42
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,080
I understand that.

43
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,630
If that's what you want,

44
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,150
I'm willing to help you.

45
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,430
Why?

46
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,240
Others come to me

47
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,150
because they want to know

48
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:06,400
if their boyfriend loves them.

49
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:09,000
But you came to me

50
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,280
because you love your boyfriend.

51
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:14,080
Most people only take.

52
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,430
But you give instead.

53
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,830
I have no reason

54
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:21,630
to say no to a good girl like you.

55
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,040
Whatever happens,

56
00:04:24,630 --> 00:04:25,950
let's fulfill your wish.

57
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:27,480
Thank you.

58
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:35,390
Clinic Room Six.

59
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:38,830
You... Why are you here?

60
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,190
Why are you here?

61
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:42,560
- Oh, I...
- Number sixty-four.

62
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,370
To clinic room six of gastroenterology.

63
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:49,310
I'd like to schedule a gastroscopy.

64
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,830
Why are you suddenly helping her?

65
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,000
She's a girl battling a serious illness.

66
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,090
All she wants is an answer.

67
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,560
I feel I should do something for her.

68
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:02,750
Aren't you afraid
our boss might find out

69
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,240
and look for an answer from you?

70
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,000
The best confession
is being true to yourself.

71
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:09,830
I really want to help her.

72
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,920
Got it.

73
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,680
I'll go with you this time.

74
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:20,680
At the crucial moment,

75
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,390
a friend's help works better
than a safety spray.

76
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:25,560
Remember

77
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,190
how I chased off those creeps?

78
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:31,270
Wham, bam!

79
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,070
Oh, okay.

80
00:05:35,390 --> 00:05:36,230
Alright then.

81
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,160
I'll be straight about it.

82
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:44,120
You're too young.

83
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,480
We're not right match.

84
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,600
How would you know if you don't even try?

85
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,270
Maybe you're actually into younger ones.

86
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:51,950
Wait, what makes you think that?

87
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:53,390
That I'm into younger people?

88
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,720
Come on, boy.

89
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:57,160
I've been through a messy one before.

90
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,000
Not planning to go through it again.

91
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:00,430
Besides,

92
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,720
we barely know each other.

93
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,800
Don't you think rushing into marriage

94
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,630
just because you're head over heels

95
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:08,310
sounds kinda naive?

96
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:10,410
Why do you say we don't know each other?

97
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:11,510
Yesterday...

98
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:16,830
Yesterday...

99
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,070
What about yesterday?

100
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,480
You didn't say that yesterday.

101
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,990
What I said in that situation
doesn't count.

102
00:06:22,990 --> 00:06:24,480
Don't take it to heart.

103
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,230
But I think,

104
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,950
you're the one I've been waiting for.

105
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,290
You're a Horse, I'm a Dog.

106
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:32,390
Dogs are perfect for Horses.

107
00:06:32,390 --> 00:06:33,660
You're a Leo, I'm a Sagittarius.

108
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:34,490
We're meant to be.

109
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,680
Hold up.

110
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,870
Leos don't buy into that nonsense.

111
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,870
Stop talking rubbish.

112
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,070
When I'm with someone else,

113
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:44,680
I don't believe that either.

114
00:06:45,190 --> 00:06:46,310
I just think,

115
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,680
you shouldn't blame the next person

116
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,830
for mistakes made by the last one, right?

117
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,560
Whether we're a good match

118
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,120
or meant to be

119
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:55,800
isn't up to anyone to decide.

120
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:57,920
It's not fair to me.

121
00:06:58,430 --> 00:07:00,240
You'll only know
when we're truly together.

122
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,600
I can't date someone that young anymore.

123
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,510
You know what I mean.

124
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,360
At your age, full of drive and energy,

125
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:07,270
you're packed with ambition.

126
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:08,870
You want to take on the whole world.

127
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,160
Getting married will only

128
00:07:11,390 --> 00:07:13,240
slow you down on your way to maturity.

129
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:15,040
So that's...

130
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,000
the conclusion you drew
from your last marriage.

131
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,390
But not everyone is that ambitious.

132
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:25,800
You've never even been married.

133
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,270
How would you know if you are or not?

134
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,940
Judging people by age

135
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:31,000
doesn't really make sense.

136
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,360
Ambition doesn't depend on age.

137
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:39,070
We should focus more on who the person is,

138
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,560
and not rely on things like

139
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:42,920
stats, numbers or whatever probabilities.

140
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,110
That's just not right.

141
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:45,270
Wait, hold on.

142
00:07:46,710 --> 00:07:48,800
I said I wanted to
date someone a bit older.

143
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:50,360
You said only someone silly

144
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:51,870
would choose their dates by age.

145
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:52,910
No.

146
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,390
That's not what I meant.

147
00:07:54,630 --> 00:07:58,070
Basically, you think I'm silly, huh?

148
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,150
No, I don't.

149
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,870
Yeah, my sweet silly one.

150
00:08:01,430 --> 00:08:02,270
You're here.

151
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:03,300
Already finished eating?

152
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:04,880
Pretty much. Let's head out.

153
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,200
Yingtao.

154
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,630
Aren't you going to introduce us?

155
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,360
I'm her boyfriend, Zeyan.

156
00:08:12,490 --> 00:08:13,360
Hi.

157
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,390
Don't talk nonsense.

158
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,640
Hey.

159
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:18,390
I'm her friend, Li Xiaoxi.

160
00:08:18,870 --> 00:08:20,680
Alright then, think it over. See you.

161
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,290
I'll wait for you at your place tonight.

162
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:26,680
Why my place? Go home to your own place.

163
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,510
I'm waiting for you.

164
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,840
Suit yourself, then.

165
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:32,840
A psychologist?

166
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:34,910
This must be tricky.

167
00:08:36,910 --> 00:08:38,670
Didn't you say you were done with all this

168
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:40,200
and wanted to focus on dating?

169
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,750
Why take on such a complicated case?

170
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,440
That girl is different.

171
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:44,510
She's worth helping.

172
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,120
How's this shirt look?

173
00:08:46,510 --> 00:08:47,390
Not great.

174
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:49,990
So I'm not the only girl

175
00:08:49,990 --> 00:08:51,550
worth your help?

176
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:54,960
Are you jealous?

177
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,390
Shouldn't I be the jealous one here?

178
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,240
Who was that just now?

179
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,910
The guy your aunt set you up with?

180
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:04,490
Yeah.

181
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:05,840
That's him.

182
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:08,870
I thought
his passion would disappear soon.

183
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,240
Now he's already talking about marriage.

184
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:13,390
Isn't that kind of scary?

185
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,520
A relationship meant for marriage,

186
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,450
what's wrong with that?

187
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:17,920
It's not good.

188
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:19,840
He's too young, I can't handle that.

189
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:22,720
Being young is a good thing.

190
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:24,600
And you're not that old.

191
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,000
You two actually make a nice couple.

192
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:27,240
How about this one?

193
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,840
It's so-so.

194
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,840
No way, being with
someone younger feels insecure.

195
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:37,080
Insecure?

196
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,280
Mm-hmm.

197
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:40,670
Want me to test him out for you?

198
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:44,000
No need to trouble yourself.

199
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,440
It's way too soon for that.

200
00:09:46,270 --> 00:09:48,120
You don't have to be polite with me.

201
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:50,480
You're the one girl
I'd actually want to help.

202
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:52,670
No.

203
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,960
Why not again?

204
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,150
He's already met you.

205
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:57,600
I'll make sure

206
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,150
he won't recognize me next time we meet.

207
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,280
Hmm.

208
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,840
No.

209
00:10:03,930 --> 00:10:04,770
Why?

210
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:05,790
I still kinda like him.

211
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,200
That's exactly why

212
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:08,630
you should get to know him more.

213
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,870
I'm just unlucky, you know?

214
00:10:12,870 --> 00:10:13,910
Once I know him well,

215
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,440
he might not be what I want.

216
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:17,120
Can you really avoid this?

217
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,240
You'll have to figure it out eventually.

218
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,120
Like…

219
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:24,390
My ex-husband?

220
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:26,240
Hmm, I thought you'd forgotten.

221
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,510
I haven't.

222
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,600
Don't mention him to me.

223
00:10:32,510 --> 00:10:33,350
You tell me.

224
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:36,600
If I had the power to see the future,

225
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:38,910
do you think I'd still be with him?

226
00:10:38,910 --> 00:10:40,240
Knowing you the way I do,

227
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:42,030
you wouldn't.

228
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,910
Yes, I wouldn't.

229
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,960
But I wouldn't want
that kind of power either.

230
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,680
Xiaoxi,

231
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,120
you know how Bai was to me.

232
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,360
You saw it yourself.

233
00:10:58,670 --> 00:11:01,080
For a while, I kept trying
to use his kindness

234
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,360
to make up for the mistakes he made.

235
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:06,960
But it didn't work.

236
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,750
That moment I saw

237
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:10,030
they were together in bed,

238
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,600
he was dead to me.

239
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:15,510
But then I thought again,

240
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:17,320
the dead one in my heart

241
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,750
was the version of him that hurt me.

242
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,270
It's just that

243
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:24,440
the places he walked through with me

244
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:26,480
and the joy we shared along the way

245
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,550
are always hard to forget.

246
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:32,030
Everywhere I go,
the memories come rushing back.

247
00:11:32,170 --> 00:11:33,460
Feels like it happened yesterday.

248
00:11:34,550 --> 00:11:36,750
Those good times were truly wonderful.

249
00:11:37,790 --> 00:11:39,000
But I can't deny

250
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,390
I really regret having gone through

251
00:11:40,390 --> 00:11:41,360
that failed marriage.

252
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,360
Looks like I missed out on quite a bit.

253
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:47,670
You'd only just started dating that guy,

254
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,110
but you've changed.

255
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,550
Changed how?

256
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,630
Honestly, I'm more like his tutor.

257
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,720
This one's adorable.

258
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:56,910
It's shaped like a steamed bun

259
00:11:56,910 --> 00:11:57,910
or more like a shaomai.

260
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:02,320
Hey, listen to me,

261
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,870
don't deny everything about him

262
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:06,360
just based on one phone call from Bei.

263
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,030
I know, I won't.

264
00:12:08,550 --> 00:12:09,440
Besides, I already knew

265
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,280
who that girl is.

266
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,030
His "little sister"?

267
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:16,240
Men calling someone
their "sister"? Suspicious.

268
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:18,000
Bei wanted me to meet that girl.

269
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,550
That shows there's nothing between them.

270
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:22,870
Then why did Bei meet her
behind your back?

271
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,150
And at night, no less.

272
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:26,150
He must have his reasons.

273
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:28,600
Like when I went with Gong to meet Guan.

274
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:29,920
The same thing, really.

275
00:12:31,030 --> 00:12:32,630
You're so inconsistent, you know that?

276
00:12:32,630 --> 00:12:34,000
A minute ago you were defending Bei

277
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,240
and now you're angrier than me.

278
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,670
Not my type. Doesn't fit.

279
00:12:39,870 --> 00:12:40,960
I told you already.

280
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,540
(Zeyan: Miss you.)
He's waiting.

281
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:46,800
(Which floor are you on? Luv u xx.)

282
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:48,550
Go on, go meet your little sweetheart.

283
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:51,670
Who said I'm meeting him?

284
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:53,160
Who has been starting

285
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:55,000
at their phone for half an hour?

286
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,390
Go on, just go.

287
00:12:57,390 --> 00:12:58,360
Alright, I'm heading out.

288
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,320
It's at ten this morning.

289
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:09,630
That's when it starts.

290
00:13:45,870 --> 00:13:47,030
Don't go inside.

291
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:48,990
I'll wait by the door.

292
00:13:49,030 --> 00:13:51,200
Ready to jump in
and save the beauty anytime.

293
00:14:02,230 --> 00:14:03,080
Hello.

294
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:04,550
Miss, do you have an appointment?

295
00:14:04,930 --> 00:14:05,770
My last name's Chen.

296
00:14:05,790 --> 00:14:06,870
Please wait a moment.

297
00:14:10,140 --> 00:14:11,460
(Chen Qing)

298
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,080
Are you Miss Chen Qing?

299
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:13,930
Yes, I am.

300
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:14,780
The second floor.

301
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:15,960
Dr. Lin is waiting.

302
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:16,800
Thank you.

303
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:23,380
(Lin Chen Psychological Counseling Center)

304
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,240
Come in, please.

305
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,600
Sorry, could you wait just a moment?

306
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:22,750
Hello.

307
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:28,240
Hello, Dr. Lin.

308
00:15:30,030 --> 00:15:30,870
Miss Chen.

309
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,720
You agreed to meet and talk with me.

310
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,670
I'm truly honored.

311
00:15:36,030 --> 00:15:38,790
I'm studying
in relationship counseling.

312
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,020
But aside from training courses,

313
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,250
I also need real case practice.

314
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:43,870
Hope we can both gain something from this.

315
00:15:44,790 --> 00:15:45,720
I hope so too.

316
00:15:46,670 --> 00:15:47,510
Please, have a seat.

317
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:57,240
I'm not an expert,
but I find psychology fascinating.

318
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:59,120
That makes me more curious

319
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:01,960
about the special case
you mentioned online.

320
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,240
Is it your friend's story

321
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:05,000
or something you experienced yourself?

322
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:05,840
Both.

323
00:16:06,390 --> 00:16:08,630
I help women
test their boyfriends' loyalty.

324
00:16:20,510 --> 00:16:21,480
When I first saw you,

325
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:23,670
I actually thought
a celebrity had walked in.

326
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:27,240
Do all psychologists talk so smoothly?

327
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,790
Or is it just you?

328
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,600
I don't know other colleagues well.

329
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,000
It's just that not every visitor

330
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,390
can manage to impress me like this.

331
00:16:35,690 --> 00:16:36,530
Thank you.

332
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:37,390
Have some tea.

333
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,550
But what really intrigues me is

334
00:16:42,550 --> 00:16:44,630
how someone as stunning as you

335
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:46,630
ends up doing something so bold.

336
00:16:47,510 --> 00:16:48,910
Dr. Lin, you sure are curious.

337
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,450
Would you like to try it yourself?

338
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,120
Don't tell me you came here today

339
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:55,550
with one of your tasks.

340
00:16:57,910 --> 00:16:58,960
Just kidding.

341
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,630
I don't have time for that.

342
00:17:02,030 --> 00:17:03,670
I haven't even figured out my own mess.

343
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:06,020
I came to see you

344
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:07,590
because I'm feeling confused

345
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:11,160
and I wanted some insight
from a psychology angle.

346
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,440
Could it be…

347
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,000
you fell for

348
00:17:15,510 --> 00:17:16,960
your client you shouldn't have?

349
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:19,750
No.

350
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:23,680
Let me put it simply.

351
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:26,550
I've seen too many scumbags up close.

352
00:17:27,310 --> 00:17:28,920
Thinking about them flirting with me

353
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,880
behind their girlfriends...

354
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:34,830
makes it hard for me to trust any guys.

355
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:37,720
I get that.

356
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,880
If there are girls going behind

357
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:41,920
her boyfriend's back to win me over,

358
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:44,310
I think I'd feel just as awful as you.

359
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,110
Really?

360
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,480
Maybe.

361
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,310
Haven't been through it, so not sure.

362
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:54,920
Those guys are crazy about you, right?

363
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:58,680
On the surface, yeah.

364
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:00,920
What do you think they like about you?

365
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:02,640
No idea.

366
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:04,720
They don't really know me at all.

367
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,400
Aside from how I look,

368
00:18:07,590 --> 00:18:09,070
what else could they possibly like?

369
00:18:10,110 --> 00:18:11,640
Do you want them to know who you are?

370
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:13,680
No need.

371
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,590
I'm not interested in any of them.

372
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,400
So you'd rather rely on looks alone

373
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,240
to win them over

374
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,510
and you managed to do that, right?

375
00:18:25,590 --> 00:18:27,480
I never planned to win anyone over.

376
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:29,590
Besides, they could choose

377
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:31,480
to ignore me, right?

378
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,480
Honestly,

379
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:35,070
that's hard to do.

380
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,030
What do you think

381
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:43,030
they really want from you?

382
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:46,000
What do you think men can get

383
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,070
from women?

384
00:18:48,790 --> 00:18:49,790
Hard to say.

385
00:18:50,110 --> 00:18:52,830
Maybe just being friends with someone

386
00:18:52,830 --> 00:18:54,920
as gorgeous as you is already enjoyable.

387
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,000
I think a pure romantic bond

388
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,400
doesn't really work

389
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,310
for most guys.

390
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,510
What about the few exceptions?

391
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,280
What are you doing?

392
00:19:10,390 --> 00:19:11,720
Wait for lightning to strike you?

393
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:14,790
You're standing so high up.

394
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,030
It should hit you first.

395
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:18,030
If it does, I'm taking you with me.

396
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:18,880
Cut the nonsense.

397
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:20,750
What are you doing here?

398
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,550
Why do you care?

399
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:23,510
What are you doing here?

400
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:24,400
I'm waiting...

401
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,160
For a friend.

402
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:27,720
A friend?

403
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,060
Wait a sec.

404
00:19:29,070 --> 00:19:30,960
Don't tell me you're the one who goes by

405
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,510
"Mianmian In Breeze".

406
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,480
Get lost. I'm just here to buy something.

407
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:35,830
Buy what? Let me see.

408
00:19:38,150 --> 00:19:39,250
Something you wouldn't need.

409
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,310
Wow, never saw that coming.

410
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:49,200
Bei Qiyuan, oh, Bei Qiyuan.

411
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:51,030
Didn't know you're a lifestyle expert.

412
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,490
Can't judge a book by its cover.

413
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:54,590
You're not embarrassed?
I am for you.

414
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:55,590
Ugh.

415
00:19:55,590 --> 00:19:56,750
So humiliating.

416
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,480
Why are you sitting down? Up, go away.

417
00:19:59,750 --> 00:20:01,590
This isn't your turf. I can sit here.

418
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:02,870
Hey,

419
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,880
aren't you hot sitting here in the sun?

420
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:08,750
Oh, good point.

421
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:26,110
What kind of men carry sun umbrellas?

422
00:20:26,550 --> 00:20:27,830
You've got so many sides to you.

423
00:20:28,270 --> 00:20:29,920
Oh, you don't know about me.

424
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,980
Good thing I ran into you.

425
00:20:36,270 --> 00:20:37,240
I need to talk to you.

426
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,410
No time for your nonsense.

427
00:20:38,410 --> 00:20:39,200
I'm seeing Mianmian.

428
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,480
Relax, I'm serious this time.

429
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:43,240
Keep it short and then leave.

430
00:20:45,550 --> 00:20:46,590
About this thing…

431
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:51,400
Stop hesitating, just say it.

432
00:20:55,830 --> 00:20:56,720
You...

433
00:20:59,070 --> 00:21:00,240
Do you like Li Xiaoxi?

434
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:15,640
How do you figure out their intentions?

435
00:21:16,350 --> 00:21:18,160
Sometimes they want to date me.

436
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:19,790
But most of them

437
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,350
skip straight to their goal.

438
00:21:22,270 --> 00:21:24,200
Has any guy ever dumped someone for you?

439
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,000
Sure have.

440
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,400
Quite a few, actually.

441
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:29,790
At least they all say they would.

442
00:21:32,480 --> 00:21:34,350
There's no real feeling
between me and her.

443
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,640
We can't properly talk before arguing.

444
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:38,350
I feel suffocated every single day.

445
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:40,000
I don't even know why.

446
00:21:40,790 --> 00:21:42,200
But I can tell you anything.

447
00:21:42,790 --> 00:21:44,110
Talking to you just feels

448
00:21:44,310 --> 00:21:46,070
relaxing and comforting.

449
00:21:47,170 --> 00:21:48,010
Really.

450
00:21:48,030 --> 00:21:48,870
Life's too short.

451
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,480
You can't fake your way through love.

452
00:21:50,660 --> 00:21:51,890
I should've broken up with her.

453
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:54,790
But I need some time.

454
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:57,830
While I wait,
I have to keep him close, you know.

455
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,200
Just the usual routine.

456
00:22:02,590 --> 00:22:03,680
Give me a bit more time.

457
00:22:04,070 --> 00:22:05,200
I've been with her for long.

458
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,550
I don't want to hurt her badly.

459
00:22:07,270 --> 00:22:08,160
Trust me.

460
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,550
Only you understand me.

461
00:22:10,070 --> 00:22:12,240
Honestly, most men who want to date me

462
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,310
just want to flirt with me

463
00:22:13,430 --> 00:22:14,590
under the guise of love.

464
00:22:16,070 --> 00:22:17,000
I know that.

465
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:19,200
How do you know?

466
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:20,880
They always test me first,

467
00:22:21,750 --> 00:22:22,960
trying to dig into my past

468
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:25,720
and telling a risqué joke or something

469
00:22:26,030 --> 00:22:28,200
just to see how I react.

470
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,240
I've heard people say

471
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:32,960
girls who bite the straw

472
00:22:33,510 --> 00:22:34,750
seem to be a bit more daring.

473
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,750
They're testing my boundaries.

474
00:22:37,270 --> 00:22:39,200
Once they realize
I'm emotionally invested,

475
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,200
the whole dating thing

476
00:22:41,830 --> 00:22:42,880
goes straight to the point.

477
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,880
Wanna go to my place tonight?

478
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:46,440
We can watch a movie.

479
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:51,030
I know all these guys who date me

480
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,550
share the same intention.

481
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:57,790
Have you ever been intimate?

482
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:59,200
No way.

483
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:01,720
When they have that kind of intention,

484
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,750
the test is basically over.

485
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,240
Their ending

486
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:08,400
is rarely a happy one.

487
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,260
Most of them end up breaking up.

488
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:12,640
The rest can't go back
to how things were.

489
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,290
That's bound to happen.

490
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,160
They know it has consequences.

491
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,400
Who else can they blame?

492
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:20,550
A guy once told me this

493
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,270
when he was venting his frustrations:

494
00:23:22,790 --> 00:23:24,240
I really envies single people.

495
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,790
They still have endless possibilities.

496
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,310
At least,

497
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:36,720
they hold a ticket to your paradise.

498
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:40,160
Do you think they deserve that?

499
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:41,170
Those guys

500
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,510
who already have girlfriends.

501
00:23:42,790 --> 00:23:45,000
That depends on how you define moving on.

502
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,240
You're more outstanding.

503
00:23:47,270 --> 00:23:48,350
Maybe they want to be with

504
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:49,880
someone better.

505
00:23:50,790 --> 00:23:52,550
By hurting the girls
who loved them deeply?

506
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,350
It serves them right.

507
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,750
I'm respectful, Bei Qiyuan.

508
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,680
Don't joke about something like that.

509
00:24:00,350 --> 00:24:01,780
Why are you taking it so seriously?

510
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,350
What I mean is,

511
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:06,110
what do you think of Li Xiaoxi?

512
00:24:06,110 --> 00:24:07,440
Do you think we're a good match?

513
00:24:10,110 --> 00:24:12,440
Of course not,
she's way too good for you.

514
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:14,240
Take a good look at yourself first.

515
00:24:16,210 --> 00:24:17,070
You've got a point.

516
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:18,310
Guess I was aiming too high.

517
00:24:19,790 --> 00:24:20,750
But the thing is

518
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:22,720
she and I have come this far already.

519
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,560
I have to

520
00:24:23,750 --> 00:24:25,000
take responsibility for her.

521
00:24:25,350 --> 00:24:26,550
How far exactly?

522
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,200
What kind of question is that?

523
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,350
It's not like you're a kid.

524
00:24:29,590 --> 00:24:30,640
She didn't turn you down?

525
00:24:31,790 --> 00:24:32,890
What are you talking about?

526
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:37,070
Wow, you really know how to enjoy life.

527
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:39,270
Where are you going?

528
00:24:39,830 --> 00:24:40,830
To seek for some wisdom.

529
00:24:43,030 --> 00:24:44,160
The reason I want to

530
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:46,030
marry her is because

531
00:24:46,030 --> 00:24:47,480
I don't want to end up like you.

532
00:24:47,870 --> 00:24:48,760
Keep dreaming.

533
00:24:48,790 --> 00:24:50,590
There's no way you could be like me.

534
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,070
Marry her if you want to.

535
00:24:52,270 --> 00:24:54,240
Have a kid soon
so I can be the godfather.

536
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:55,140
Come here, sit down.

537
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,110
Come on, take a seat.

538
00:24:56,110 --> 00:24:57,310
Let's sit down and talk, okay?

539
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,200
How should I put it?

540
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,440
Help me sort this out.

541
00:25:04,350 --> 00:25:06,480
The reason I want to marry her sooner

542
00:25:06,910 --> 00:25:07,800
is because

543
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,000
the time we've been together

544
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:12,310
is not exactly short

545
00:25:12,310 --> 00:25:13,350
or long either.

546
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,250
If I bring up marriage with her...

547
00:25:17,830 --> 00:25:18,670
Go on.

548
00:25:20,310 --> 00:25:22,030
From what I know about Li Xiaoxi,

549
00:25:22,050 --> 00:25:23,270
she's got a strong personality

550
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:24,480
and she values her freedom.

551
00:25:25,610 --> 00:25:26,450
So I'm worried that

552
00:25:26,470 --> 00:25:28,240
she's not ready to get married that soon.

553
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:30,790
But even if we did get married,

554
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:32,640
I'd still give her personal space.

555
00:25:32,790 --> 00:25:33,720
I'm fine with that.

556
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:35,030
I really respect her.

557
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:37,030
If she doesn't want kids yet, I can wait.

558
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,240
Even if she doesn't...

559
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:41,070
It's just marriage, right?

560
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,830
You can simply ask her.

561
00:25:44,350 --> 00:25:45,270
What if she says no?

562
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:47,590
Yeah, fair point.

563
00:25:48,510 --> 00:25:49,830
It's not like grocery shopping,

564
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:51,400
You can't get turned down every time.

565
00:25:51,830 --> 00:25:53,160
You've thought this through, huh?

566
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:54,440
Thanks for that.

567
00:25:56,070 --> 00:25:56,920
Actually,

568
00:25:58,600 --> 00:25:59,840
you don't really know about her.

569
00:26:01,700 --> 00:26:02,550
What do you mean?

570
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:03,500
Treat me another day

571
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:04,610
and I'll give you a lesson.

572
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:06,070
Now move. I'm waiting for Mianmian.

573
00:26:06,070 --> 00:26:07,400
Don't rush off, tell me now.

574
00:26:08,030 --> 00:26:09,270
A few words, then you leave.

575
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:10,320
Go on, I'm listening.

576
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,200
She's independent

577
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,480
because most of the time

578
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:15,680
she has to rely on herself.

579
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:17,200
Think about it.

580
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:18,400
When you were together,

581
00:26:18,590 --> 00:26:19,680
was there ever a time

582
00:26:19,830 --> 00:26:22,240
she didn't cling to you like a lamb.

583
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,400
She wants every time you meet

584
00:26:27,550 --> 00:26:29,310
to feel like a romantic date.

585
00:26:30,510 --> 00:26:32,110
She's afraid that as time goes by,

586
00:26:32,110 --> 00:26:33,790
her flaws might slip out unintentionally.

587
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:35,310
And you'll see she's not perfect.

588
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,880
Whether I like him or not doesn't matter.

589
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:39,830
As long as he likes me,

590
00:26:41,070 --> 00:26:42,270
I'm willing to give it a try.

591
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:44,210
She wants to understand you

592
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,550
and then adjust herself

593
00:26:46,030 --> 00:26:47,640
to show you her better version.

594
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,240
Whether you marry her

595
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,110
or have kids with her,

596
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:51,960
none of that matters much to her.

597
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:53,080
What she truly wants

598
00:26:53,090 --> 00:26:54,790
is simply a stable home.

599
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:57,880
Marriage

600
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,160
is probably something she'd love

601
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,640
for you to bring up first.

602
00:27:09,830 --> 00:27:10,790
What's wrong?

603
00:27:13,310 --> 00:27:14,270
Why do I feel like

604
00:27:14,550 --> 00:27:15,960
you know Li Xiaoxi better than I do?

605
00:27:18,350 --> 00:27:19,510
Can you not ramble?

606
00:27:19,510 --> 00:27:20,640
Women I've flirted with

607
00:27:20,830 --> 00:27:22,440
are more than
the Pokémon you've caught.

608
00:27:22,590 --> 00:27:24,200
Think I don't know what they're thinking?

609
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,270
Seems like you know women

610
00:27:30,270 --> 00:27:31,680
better than I do.

611
00:27:32,110 --> 00:27:34,110
I don't get women.

612
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:38,960
You are one.

613
00:27:45,350 --> 00:27:46,680
Sometimes I wonder,

614
00:27:48,790 --> 00:27:50,200
if I were a woman,

615
00:27:51,350 --> 00:27:52,480
someone beautiful,

616
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:53,790
smart,

617
00:27:54,110 --> 00:27:55,310
and kind-hearted,

618
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:58,830
and I fell for a man,

619
00:28:00,030 --> 00:28:01,270
head over heels,

620
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:05,840
tell me,

621
00:28:06,550 --> 00:28:07,640
how would I explain

622
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:09,440
my grand relationship history to him?

623
00:28:12,310 --> 00:28:13,480
Here's my suggestion.

624
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:15,160
Just turn it into a comic.

625
00:28:16,070 --> 00:28:19,310
Call it
"One Thousand and One Nights of Impulse".

626
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,350
Ugh, naughty.

627
00:28:23,310 --> 00:28:24,640
My past...

628
00:28:26,030 --> 00:28:27,550
I'm terrified you'll find out about it.

629
00:28:29,790 --> 00:28:31,680
But I want to be upfront with you.

630
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:33,750
I love

631
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,270
the feeling of being in love.

632
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:48,280
For me,

633
00:28:48,910 --> 00:28:49,750
I just love

634
00:28:49,750 --> 00:28:51,680
the feeling of being loved
by someone I love.

635
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:53,270
Are you out of your mind?

636
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,920
What's wrong with you?

637
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:55,790
Can you act normal?

638
00:28:58,070 --> 00:28:59,110
Also,

639
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,550
do you actually want me to fall for you

640
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,240
or are you trying to make me give up?

641
00:29:06,030 --> 00:29:07,550
So you'll never fall in love

642
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:10,920
with a girl like me, right?

643
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:12,590
What do you mean?

644
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:14,110
Answer me now.

645
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:15,790
I suspect

646
00:29:16,110 --> 00:29:17,030
you've met another you,

647
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:18,720
a female version of Gong.

648
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:20,350
I'm not that lucky.

649
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:22,240
I'm writing a story
and wanted your input.

650
00:29:22,510 --> 00:29:23,350
Come on.

651
00:29:24,830 --> 00:29:25,960
I think

652
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:28,720
most men wouldn't be okay with it.

653
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:31,510
Jealous?

654
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:37,920
Seems women shouldn't share this
with men.

655
00:29:39,550 --> 00:29:41,030
Partly because of jealousy,

656
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:43,550
partly insecurity.

657
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:44,590
I feel

658
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,270
they fear their partners

659
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,830
have experienced better love before

660
00:29:48,270 --> 00:29:49,400
and won't value them.

661
00:29:49,750 --> 00:29:51,070
In short, they're afraid to lose.

662
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:52,830
So, which type are you?

663
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:56,980
I used to be the first kind.

664
00:29:58,830 --> 00:29:59,750
Old gentleman,

665
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,270
have you already moved past

666
00:30:01,270 --> 00:30:02,590
the age of getting jealous?

667
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:03,790
Maybe.

668
00:30:04,270 --> 00:30:06,030
Now I believe
that as long as you love her,

669
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,480
no matter what kind of past she's had,

670
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:10,240
you'll find a way

671
00:30:10,510 --> 00:30:11,640
to accept everything.

672
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:19,200
Wow.

673
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:21,830
I swear, behind you,

674
00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:24,480
I can almost see
the Halo of the Saint glowing.

675
00:30:24,750 --> 00:30:25,680
A scumbag like you

676
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:27,070
would never get it.

677
00:30:27,790 --> 00:30:28,830
You really believe that?

678
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,480
To me, a relationship

679
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:31,720
is like two people stranded

680
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:33,070
on a deserted island,

681
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,350
where nobody else's opinion

682
00:30:34,350 --> 00:30:35,310
really matters.

683
00:30:35,550 --> 00:30:37,110
There's no betrayal, only each other.

684
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:38,790
But we live in

685
00:30:38,790 --> 00:30:40,480
a city packed with people everywhere.

686
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:41,590
Doesn't matter.

687
00:30:41,830 --> 00:30:42,790
As long as you love her,

688
00:30:43,030 --> 00:30:44,000
no one else compares.

689
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,350
She's the only one you see.

690
00:30:46,310 --> 00:30:47,830
So, Mr. Lonely,

691
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:50,350
you don't care how many scandals she has?

692
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:54,310
What would I need those scandals for?

693
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,510
You're becoming more and more like me.

694
00:31:04,350 --> 00:31:06,720
Thank you for your patient lessons.

695
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,640
Well, you're a good student.

696
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:10,560
Miss Chen,

697
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,350
I've got another appointment.

698
00:31:12,750 --> 00:31:13,590
How about

699
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,110
we wrap things up for today?

700
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:16,510
That soon?

701
00:31:17,310 --> 00:31:19,200
Seems you're not a fan of

702
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:20,160
the stories I share.

703
00:31:21,310 --> 00:31:22,160
Quite the opposite.

704
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:25,000
This story is truly unique.

705
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:26,440
And it's a great example.

706
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,350
There's so much worth discussing.

707
00:31:29,110 --> 00:31:30,750
It's sparked a lot of thoughts for me.

708
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:32,000
If you're open to it,

709
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:33,240
we can meet again,

710
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:34,880
find a more relaxed time slot,

711
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:36,030
and dive into the topic.

712
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:38,720
Of course.

713
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,200
How about we change the venue next time?

714
00:31:42,590 --> 00:31:43,440
Why's that?

715
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:46,310
I'm not fond of chatting
in such a formal place.

716
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:48,240
Besides, this happens to be

717
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,440
your turf, Dr. Lin.

718
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:50,680
How would I know

719
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:52,310
if this place might have something

720
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:53,480
that creates illusions

721
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:54,960
or some hidden hypnotic gadget?

722
00:31:55,350 --> 00:31:56,720
Such imagination.

723
00:32:00,270 --> 00:32:01,550
Where would you like to go?

724
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:03,720
Where would you like to go?

725
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,390
I like going to the movies.

726
00:32:08,390 --> 00:32:09,720
But that's not a good spot for...

727
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:10,560
Alright.

728
00:32:10,750 --> 00:32:11,720
Let's do the movie then.

729
00:32:12,110 --> 00:32:14,160
We can talk more after the film.

730
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:15,550
What do you think?

731
00:32:20,550 --> 00:32:21,350
We've talked enough.

732
00:32:21,350 --> 00:32:22,290
My mouth's dry. Come on.

733
00:32:22,290 --> 00:32:23,880
Where are we going? My bag.

734
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:26,880
I've been talking.

735
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:27,830
Treat me to a drink.

736
00:32:27,830 --> 00:32:29,350
A jumbo boba and sago milk tea.

737
00:32:29,350 --> 00:32:30,480
With grass jelly and pudding.

738
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:31,790
But I'm on keto right now.

739
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:32,660
So make it half sugar.

740
00:32:32,660 --> 00:32:33,750
You're not waiting for her?

741
00:32:34,110 --> 00:32:34,960
For who?

742
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,030
Mianmian.

743
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:49,510
Miss Chen.

744
00:32:50,410 --> 00:32:51,270
Screw her.

745
00:32:51,270 --> 00:32:52,880
A woman who stands me up.

746
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:53,720
Here comes the taxi.

747
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:54,600
Where are we heading?

748
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:55,790
Let's see how sincere you are.

749
00:32:55,790 --> 00:32:57,030
I drove here.

750
00:32:57,680 --> 00:32:58,680
Please reach out to me

751
00:32:58,680 --> 00:32:59,830
to book Dr. Lin next time.

752
00:33:00,110 --> 00:33:01,030
Alright, thank you.

753
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:07,540
Being the good guy is tough.

754
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:30,520
On both sides.

755
00:33:30,520 --> 00:33:32,440
We need to widen by three to five cm.

756
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:33,600
Uh-huh.

757
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:35,680
- That gives it a contour.
- Yes, exactly.

758
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,000
Yu.

759
00:33:38,590 --> 00:33:39,790
Mr. Xiu.

760
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:41,840
Hello.

761
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:43,000
Hello.

762
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:45,240
These are all your favorite dishes.

763
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:47,480
Try them,
see if my cooking's gotten worse.

764
00:33:51,030 --> 00:33:52,440
Aren't you going to eat?

765
00:33:53,110 --> 00:33:55,160
Fine, I won't have any of this love stuff.

766
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:56,290
Bye, Mr. Xiu.

767
00:33:56,310 --> 00:33:57,150
Bye-bye.

768
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:03,790
Don't call me that in front of my staff.

769
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,790
Didn't we agree to start fresh?

770
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:07,830
When we started dating,

771
00:34:07,830 --> 00:34:09,000
I always called you Yu.

772
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:10,770
Well, how long

773
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,400
has it been since you called me that?

774
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:25,400
It's way too greasy for me.

775
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,000
I can't eat it.

776
00:34:27,150 --> 00:34:28,410
But this is twice-cooked pork.

777
00:34:28,410 --> 00:34:29,280
Your favorite.

778
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,630
You always asked me to cook it.

779
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,590
That was years ago.

780
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,880
My lifestyle's messy,
my stomach's not great.

781
00:34:36,030 --> 00:34:37,510
Greasy food makes me uncomfortable.

782
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:41,230
Come to think of it.

783
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:42,840
How would you even know?

784
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:48,360
So what do you like?
I'll get it for you.

785
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:52,070
What do you think

786
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:53,880
I like to eat now?

787
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:00,320
I…

788
00:35:01,030 --> 00:35:01,880
Honestly…

789
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:03,710
I have no idea.

790
00:35:07,280 --> 00:35:08,150
You should head back.

791
00:35:08,280 --> 00:35:09,360
The store needs you.

792
00:35:09,590 --> 00:35:10,710
I'll pick you up after work.

793
00:35:10,710 --> 00:35:11,680
We'll have a proper meal.

794
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:12,800
We'll see.

795
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:14,720
Mom.

796
00:35:15,070 --> 00:35:16,550
Mom? What brings you here?

797
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:18,840
I passed by on my way to the bank.

798
00:35:19,710 --> 00:35:22,190
Figured you've been too busy
to eat properly.

799
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:24,590
So I brought some porridge.

800
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,160
Hey.

801
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:27,920
Guess who I ran into at the bank?

802
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:29,960
Hua.

803
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:31,760
Hua!

804
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:33,220
Come here!

805
00:35:33,230 --> 00:35:34,760
Hua's loaded, go for him.

806
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:36,630
Your mom likes him, hurry up and go!

807
00:35:37,550 --> 00:35:38,960
I told you she'd be here.

808
00:35:39,550 --> 00:35:40,440
Come on, come on.

809
00:35:41,710 --> 00:35:43,630
You two haven't seen each other in ages.

810
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:52,920
Yeah, it's been a while.

811
00:35:56,230 --> 00:35:57,070
Ah.

812
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:59,190
This is my husband. You've met before.

813
00:36:05,150 --> 00:36:06,840
I ran into your mother at the bank.

814
00:36:07,190 --> 00:36:09,070
So I gave her a ride here on the way.

815
00:36:09,710 --> 00:36:11,230
Good thing I bumped into Hua.

816
00:36:11,230 --> 00:36:13,070
He even recommended me a finance plan.

817
00:36:14,510 --> 00:36:15,510
Oh right, Xiu,

818
00:36:15,510 --> 00:36:18,070
stop spending
on flashy, pointless stuff

819
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:19,440
just to make Yu happy.

820
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,690
You won't save a dime that way.

821
00:36:20,880 --> 00:36:22,110
You need to manage your money.

822
00:36:25,070 --> 00:36:25,920
Mom.

823
00:36:26,230 --> 00:36:27,960
Who said we didn't save any money?

824
00:36:28,630 --> 00:36:30,440
Xiu's got a few songs trending lately.

825
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:31,440
It gets a lot of likes.

826
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:34,400
He gets royalties every month.

827
00:36:34,670 --> 00:36:36,670
Likes? I don't get that stuff.

828
00:36:37,150 --> 00:36:39,800
If he's making money,
why are you still so busy?

829
00:36:40,510 --> 00:36:41,630
Hua's one of our own.

830
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:43,230
I've watched him grow up.

831
00:36:43,710 --> 00:36:45,270
Ask him if you're unsure about finance.

832
00:36:45,270 --> 00:36:46,230
He's an expert.

833
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:47,240
Ma'am,

834
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:48,630
investing always has risks.

835
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:50,360
I can't give you any guarantees.

836
00:36:51,590 --> 00:36:53,110
You're just being too modest.

837
00:36:54,630 --> 00:36:55,480
I've got a meeting.

838
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:56,880
I'll head out first.

839
00:36:57,050 --> 00:36:57,910
Alright.

840
00:36:58,030 --> 00:36:59,190
Take care of your work.

841
00:36:59,190 --> 00:37:00,030
Hey.

842
00:37:00,150 --> 00:37:01,960
Come over for a meal
when you've got time.

843
00:37:02,510 --> 00:37:04,440
I'll make your favorite braised noodles.

844
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:05,800
- Sure.
- See you.

845
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:08,230
See you.

846
00:37:09,150 --> 00:37:10,030
I'm heading out.

847
00:37:10,030 --> 00:37:10,870
Take care.

848
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:12,360
Come visit us sometime.

849
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:13,200
Sure.

850
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:15,150
Mom, let me walk you out.

851
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:16,300
- No need.
- No need.

852
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:22,480
Drink your porridge before it cools down.

853
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:26,230
Why are you eating something so greasy?

854
00:37:28,190 --> 00:37:29,670
I just missed the taste.

855
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,840
Xiu made it and brought it over.

856
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:34,320
You know her stomach's upset, right?

857
00:37:34,550 --> 00:37:36,000
But I still deserve good food.

858
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:38,000
I like it, that's all.

859
00:37:43,880 --> 00:37:45,000
Alright then, I'll get going.

860
00:37:45,390 --> 00:37:46,270
Go ahead.

861
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:47,400
Come home early tonight.

862
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:48,240
Alright.

863
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:58,760
Hey, stop eating those.

864
00:37:58,760 --> 00:37:59,600
Have some porridge.

865
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:03,630
Isn't this a takeout?

866
00:38:05,590 --> 00:38:07,480
But it's good for your stomach, my lady.

867
00:38:11,550 --> 00:38:12,670
Hello, Ms. Li.

868
00:38:13,550 --> 00:38:15,590
Have you already met him?

869
00:38:16,030 --> 00:38:17,320
I just came back from seeing him.

870
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:18,840
How did it feel?

871
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:20,630
I think he's pretty nice.

872
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:22,710
He's cultured and has a sense of humor.

873
00:38:23,180 --> 00:38:24,380
You two would get along well.

874
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:25,670
So…

875
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:28,110
Do you think he...

876
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:30,230
has any feelings for you?

877
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:33,000
He treated me as a case study.

878
00:38:33,510 --> 00:38:35,280
Our first meeting felt like an interview.

879
00:38:35,510 --> 00:38:36,760
What feelings could there be?

880
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:39,880
So…

881
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:43,400
I think you would be able to tell

882
00:38:44,110 --> 00:38:46,440
if he likes you.

883
00:38:47,710 --> 00:38:49,550
He doesn't seem to dislike me.

884
00:38:49,880 --> 00:38:51,000
Beyond that, I can't say.

885
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:52,440
Fair enough.

886
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:54,590
He's a psychology major.

887
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:57,230
Getting to know him isn't exactly easy.

888
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:00,110
But he can read people in a second.

889
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:04,000
I feel transparent when I'm around him.

890
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:09,190
So, Ms. Li,

891
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,440
you really have to be careful.

892
00:39:12,030 --> 00:39:13,500
Don't let him turn the tables on you.

893
00:39:14,070 --> 00:39:15,440
Promise me, don't forget

894
00:39:15,630 --> 00:39:16,760
why you came to me.

895
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:19,760
Mm-hmm.

896
00:39:20,590 --> 00:39:21,590
But…

897
00:39:22,550 --> 00:39:24,960
Ms. Li, I want you to understand,

898
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:28,480
I just want to know who he really is.

899
00:39:30,030 --> 00:39:31,840
If anything happens, I'll let you know.

900
00:39:32,550 --> 00:39:33,670
Don't overthink it, okay?

901
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:34,640
Mm.

902
00:39:34,790 --> 00:39:35,650
Bye.

903
00:39:35,670 --> 00:39:36,800
Mm, bye.

904
00:39:38,620 --> 00:39:44,300
(Mu)

905
00:39:44,300 --> 00:39:45,980
(Yingtao)

906
00:39:45,980 --> 00:39:47,740
(No answer)

907
00:39:47,740 --> 00:39:48,620
(Voice call)

908
00:39:48,940 --> 00:39:49,780
(Yingtao)

909
00:39:52,030 --> 00:39:52,960
Hey, Xiaoxi.

910
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:55,400
How's it going with your sweetheart?

911
00:39:56,710 --> 00:39:58,030
Come on, spill.

912
00:39:58,030 --> 00:39:59,880
Are you seeing other women?

913
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:01,320
Huh?

914
00:40:02,070 --> 00:40:03,990
A woman came to the flower shop today.

915
00:40:03,990 --> 00:40:05,440
She wanted to invite you to dinner.

916
00:40:14,801 --> 00:40:17,400
♪I'll admit♪

917
00:40:17,401 --> 00:40:21,440
♪My back is faced against the wall♪

918
00:40:22,321 --> 00:40:26,187
♪There's nothing that
I wouldn't try to do♪

919
00:40:26,212 --> 00:40:30,400
♪For this feeling to have you♪

920
00:40:30,681 --> 00:40:32,880
♪I'll resist♪

921
00:40:33,201 --> 00:40:35,215
♪Your gaze, your lips♪

922
00:40:35,240 --> 00:40:37,400
♪Your touches again♪

923
00:40:38,281 --> 00:40:42,261
♪There's no one that
I wouldn't try to fool♪

924
00:40:42,286 --> 00:40:45,320
♪For an image of you♪

925
00:40:46,321 --> 00:40:48,760
♪Take my hand again♪

926
00:40:48,761 --> 00:40:50,520
♪Take my mind again♪

927
00:40:50,601 --> 00:40:53,960
♪Break into my heart again♪

928
00:40:54,361 --> 00:40:56,538
♪I'm falling out again♪

929
00:40:56,563 --> 00:40:58,400
♪I'm on my knees again♪

930
00:40:58,401 --> 00:41:02,240
♪To beg for the truth♪

931
00:41:04,081 --> 00:41:08,240
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

932
00:41:08,241 --> 00:41:13,240
♪Is that the secret to love♪

933
00:41:13,601 --> 00:41:16,560
♪I thought it had came from
below us♪

934
00:41:16,641 --> 00:41:20,040
♪Did it come from above♪

935
00:41:20,121 --> 00:41:23,880
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

936
00:41:24,121 --> 00:41:29,200
♪Is that the secret to love♪

937
00:41:29,601 --> 00:41:32,040
♪Is it violent or warming, entrancing♪

938
00:41:32,041 --> 00:41:36,480
♪This secret of love♪
